Scheme Finder AI-Powered Multilingual  Government Scheme Discovery System 
Abstract 
Scheme Finder is an intelligent, multilingual, and voice-enabled web application designed to  simplify access to government welfare schemes. The system integrates Artificial Intelligence  (AI) for intent recognition, multilingual content management, voice-based search, and text to-speech functionality. 
Unlike traditional government portals that require manual browsing and prior knowledge,  Scheme Finder allows users to simply type or speak their needs, and the system intelligently  filters relevant schemes. 
This project focuses on accessibility, inclusivity, and smart digital governance support. 
Introduction 
Government schemes are often difficult to navigate due to: 
∙ Complex websites 
∙ Language barriers 
∙ Information overload 
∙ Lack of personalization 
∙ Low digital literacy 
Scheme Finder addresses these challenges by creating a user-centric, AI-assisted platform  that makes discovering schemes easier and faster. 
Objectives 
∙ Provide a centralized platform for scheme discovery 
∙ Implement AI-based intent recognition 
∙ Support multilingual users 
∙ Enable voice interaction 
∙ Improve accessibility for rural and elderly users 
∙ Create a scalable and future-ready system
System Overview 
The system works in five major steps: 
1. User inputs query (Text or Voice) 
2. AI API analyzes user intent 
3. Category is detected 
4. Schemes are filtered dynamically 
5. Results are displayed with optional text-to-speech 
